%YAML 1.1
%TAG !u! tag:unity3d.com,2011:
--- !u!114 &11400000
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 8eb9d9fa0ccbe1b4cbcd2a1d889b806b, type: 3}
  m_Name: FirstDayMainConversation
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::Dialogue
  conversationName: FirstDayMainConversation
  lines:
  - speakerName: ???
    line: 'Ah! There you are-- my newest and most <i>contractually entrapped</i>
      employee! Good evening, and welcome to the MaCray hotel. '
  - speakerName: ???
    line: I am the owner of this esteemed hotel-- and since you signed that contract
      I gave you, I'm also your boss. Welcome aboard! You can call me Randy.
  - speakerName: Randy
    line: You'll have the honor of being my employee for the next <b>10 days</b>,
      and I expect you to reach the end without ending your employment... <i>prematurely</i>.
      Finding replacements gets rather tedious.
  - speakerName: Randy
    line: So, are you ready for your first day-- or night, rather-- on the job? There
      is much to do.
  - speakerName: Randy
    line: Hm? Feeling a little nervous? Oh, how cute.
  - speakerName: Randy
    line: Don't worry, I will make sure to keep a <i>close eye on you</i> to ensure
      you're getting the hang of things. Let my <i>constant, scrutinizing</i> gaze
      comfort you and guide you to success!
  - speakerName: Randy
    line: As stated in your work contract, you will remain in the hotel for 10 days
      and carry out the responsibilities that were outlined in said contract.
  - speakerName: Randy
    line: Once you have successfully worked for all 10 days, you will be free to
      go.
  - speakerName: Randy
    line: As you have probably noticed, you will be working nights at the hotel.
      The hotel is very quiet at this time, wonderfully free of pesky guests wandering
      around and... seeing things they shouldn't.
  - speakerName: Randy
    line: The kind of work you will be doing is easier to do at night, so make sure
      you finish work before morning comes! That is when a fresh batch of produc--
      I mean <i>guests</i>-- will come to check in.
  - speakerName: Randy
    line: ...Hm? What <i>are</i> your responsibilities?
  - speakerName: Randy
    line: Ah yes, I forgot-- you signed the contract before reading it! Heh heh,
      how incredibly foolish of you.
  - speakerName: Randy
    line: I suppose there is no use in sugar coating it. Your job is to <b>harvest
      organs and other organic materials</b> from the human guests that stay at the
      hotel, and then <b>sell those materials</b> to the <i>special</i> clientele
      that are waiting in the gift shop.
  - speakerName: Randy
    line: Oh, please, don't look so horrified. You didn't think humans were the <i>only
      ones</i> who wanted to purchase goods from other creatures, did you? Haha!
  - speakerName: Randy
    line: There are plenty of... <i>other</i> creatures in this world with money
      to spend-- and they all have a <i>monstrous</i> appetite for human material,
      heh heh.
  - speakerName: Randy
    line: They come from far and wide to get their hands on the rare human products
      that are for sale at this hotel.
  - speakerName: Randy
    line: Whether they eat them, make potions with them, whatever-- it's not our
      concern. We just stock the shelves and make money.
  - speakerName: Randy
    line: The types of goods we sell here are difficult to find on the... <i>public</i>
      markets, as I'm sure you can understand. This gives us an excellent business
      opportunity to fill the market gap.
  - speakerName: Randy
    line: Ah, I see all the color has drained from your cheeks... If you plan to
      pass out, please do it outside of work hours, on your own time. And don't bother
      trying to escape-- I can assure you, it won't work.
  - speakerName: Randy
    line: Now, I am indeed aware that you are human-- just like the unsuspecting
      guests who stay at this hotel; however, your position as my employee will prevent
      you from becoming an... <i>organ donor</i>, shall I say.
  - speakerName: Randy
    line: So as long as you have this job, you have nothing to worry about!
  - speakerName: Randy
    line: Regarding the guests you will be harvesting from, I have already taken
      the liberty of... <i>preparing</i> them. You will find them in their rooms,
      ready for harvesting.
  - speakerName: Randy
    line: You don't have to worry about helping the guests with their 'departure'--
      I'll always handle that part before your shift starts.
  - speakerName: Randy
    line: Now, listen closely-- this hotel has a reputation to uphold for quality
      goods and excellent service; therefore, I have high standards.
  - speakerName: Randy
    line: To ensure you are reaching those standards, you will have a <b>daily quota</b>
      for the amount of money you must make by the end of your shift.
  - speakerName: Randy
    line: I must measure your job performance somehow, yes?
  - speakerName: Randy
    line: Tonight, your <b>quota is (insert quota here)</b>. I have given you a reasonable
      goal to reach for your first day; However, understand that the quota will be
      higher every day.
  - speakerName: Randy
    line: I don't have to explain to you what will happen if you fail to reach quota,
      correct? A satisfactory job performance will give you more than just job security--
      it will lengthen your life, heh heh.
  repeatLine:
    speakerName: Randy
    line: Don't you have something else better to do?
